# src/LTX-2 — Local Fork Rules

`src/LTX-2` is a **maintained local fork** of the upstream LTX-2 library. It is not a read-only dependency.

## One rule for what goes here

Before touching anything in `src/LTX-2`, ask:

> **Could a different experiment ever need this?**

- **Yes** → add it to `src/LTX-2` (general, reusable capability)
- **No** → it belongs in `experiments/exp_XXX/run.py` only

## Every change must be

1. **Additive.** New functions or new optional parameters with backward-compatible defaults. Never change an existing signature.
2. **General-purpose.** No experiment names, no hardcoded paths, no research-question-specific logic inside the library.
3. **Documented in `src/LTX-2/CHANGES.md`** — immediately, in the same edit session.

## CHANGES.md is mandatory

Every time you add or modify anything in `src/LTX-2`, append an entry to `src/LTX-2/CHANGES.md` with:
- Date
- Which file(s) changed
- What was added/changed and why (one sentence)
- The new signature if it is a function

This file exists so upstream upgrades can be re-applied cleanly without diffing.

## What stays in experiments/

- Config-specific computations (e.g. `compute_clip_frame_idx`)
- Pipeline call sites and argument assembly
- Anything that references a specific experiment number or dataset path
